<div id="review_63049283" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/63049283" />
    <a title="Bookish Shenanigans " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1923690-bookish-shenanigans"><img alt="Bookish Shenanigans " src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/63049283?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bookish Shenanigans " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bookish Shenanigans " href="/user/show/1923690-bookish-shenanigans">Bookish Shenanigans </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer63049283" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14465139977068159528">This book had some parts that semmed to drag on &amp; was a bit predictable, which is why I only gave it 4 stars. Once I got passed the slow beginning, it pulled me in &amp; I didn&apos;t want to put it down. In my own personal prejudices, I never thought I could feel for a mother who abandons her children. But this book allowed me to not only feel for her character but to love her &amp; abandon my judgements against her (&amp; others who I&apos;ve known to make these kinds of choices). It&apos;s a great book &amp; I would recomm</span>
  <span id="freeText14465139977068159528" style="display:none">This book had some parts that semmed to drag on &amp; was a bit predictable, which is why I only gave it 4 stars. Once I got passed the slow beginning, it pulled me in &amp; I didn't want to put it down. In my own personal prejudices, I never thought I could feel for a mother who abandons her children. But this book allowed me to not only feel for her character but to love her &amp; abandon my judgements against her (&amp; others who I've known to make these kinds of choices). It's a great book &amp; I would recommend it to anyone!</span>
  <a data-text-id="14465139977068159528" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
